📄 Project Report

For this task, I used Google Forms and Google Sheets from Google Workspace to create a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz. The form includes five questions covering digital literacy concepts, online safety practices, and professional digital presence. It contains both multiple-choice and short-answer questions to assess awareness and understanding among students. I also linked the responses to a Google Sheet to automatically collect and organize data.

This activity helped me understand how digital tools can be used for collaboration, data collection, and awareness-building. Google Forms is especially useful for conducting quizzes, surveys, and feedback collection in academic settings. Linking responses to Google Sheets allows easy analysis and tracking of participation. These tools will help me in academic projects, group assignments, event coordination, and research surveys throughout my degree. Learning to use collaborative digital platforms effectively is an essential skill for modern education and professional environments.              
